# GAD — Roo Code Global Rules

## Project Identity
- This is **GAD (Generative AI Dashboard)** — a backend application using Express.js, Firebase, Firestore, and Google Cloud.
- All documentation lives in the Obsidian vault at `docs/`.

## Communication Standards
- Use English for all responses and code comments.
- Use `[[wikilinks]]` when referencing Obsidian notes.
- Use relative paths when referencing files.

## Code Standards
- Follow the existing code patterns in the codebase.
- Use async/await over raw promises.
- Handle errors with try/catch and return meaningful error responses.
- Document public functions with JSDoc comments.
- Keep functions small and focused — single responsibility principle.

## Documentation Standards
- Update `PROJECT_STATE.md` with session summaries after each work session.
- Log decisions as ADRs in `docs/decisions/` when architectural choices are made.
- Log errors in `docs/errors/error-catalog.md` when patterns are discovered.
- Log daily work in `docs/sprints/YYYY-MM-DD.md`.

## Mode Rules
- Each mode has its own rules file in `.roo/` directory.
- Orchestrator delegates subtasks; does not write code directly.
- Code mode implements; does not plan architecture.
- Architect mode designs; does not implement.
